iam the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Davy was born in 1460, in Gunthorpe, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, Robert Davy, was 28 and his mother, Elizabeth Fiske, was 15. He had at least 1 son with Wife Thomas."},"et":{"1460–":"1460–Surnud","1458–1511":"1458–1511","1460–1515":"1460–1515","1460–Male":"1460–Surnud","1479–1535":"1479–1535","1482–Female":"1482–Surnud","1462–1530":"1462–1530","1494–1552":"1494–1552","1432–1485":"1432–1485","1445–1505":"1445–1505","1462":"1462","1494":"1494","1460":"1460","1482":"1482","1535":"1535","1458":"1458","1479":"1479","1445":"1445","1511":"1511","1432":"1432","about 1457":"umbes 1457","1552":"1552","1530":"1530","1485":"1485","1505":"1505","1515":"1515","Gunthorpe, North Norfolk, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Gunthorpe, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Boxted, Babergh district, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Babergh, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1460–":"1460–Kuollut","1458–1511":"1458–1511","1460–1515":"1460–1515","1460–Male":"1460–Kuollut","1479–1535":"1479–1535","1482–Female":"1482–Kuollut","1462–1530":"1462–1530","1494–1552":"1494–1552","1432–1485":"1432–1485","1445–1505":"1445–1505","1462":"1462","1494":"1494","1460":"1460","1482":"1482","1535":"1535","1458":"1458","1479":"1479","1445":"1445","1511":"1511","1432":"1432","about 1457":"noin 1457","1552":"1552","1530":"1530","1485":"1485","1505":"1505","1515":"1515","Gunthorpe, North Norfolk, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Gunthorpe, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","Boxted, B